    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.5.7">
<l>pēṇāta valiyarakkar meliya vaṉṟu peruvaraittōḷiṟanerittaṉ ṟavuṇark kōṉai</l>
<l>pūṇākam piḷaveṭutta pōrval lōṉaip porukaṭaluḷ tuyilamarnta puḷḷūr tiyai</l>
<l>yūṇākap pēymulainañ cuṇṭāṉ taṉṉai yuḷḷuvā ruḷḷattē yuṟaikiṉ ṟāṉai</l>
<l>kāṇātu tiritaruvēṉ kaṇṭu koṇṭēṉ kaṭipoḻilcūḻ kaṭaṉmallait talaca yaṉattē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The one skilled in battle who, having once crushed</l>
<l rend="indent">the disrespectful, strong demon so that [his] huge boulder[-like] arms</l>
<l rend="indent">dropped off [and he] weakened,</l>
<l>Once lifted a demon king’s jeweled chest so to split [it],</l>
<l rend="indent">that bird-rider who rests in repose in the crashing sea,</l>
<l>The one who ate poison as food from the demon’s broad breasts,</l>
<l rend="indent">him who dwells in the hearts of those who contemplate him,</l>
<l>I, who wandered aimlessly without seeing, saw for myself in Talacayaṉam</l>
<l rend="indent">encircled by fragrant gardens at Mallai by the sea.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
